            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> That's not possible since the query formatter cannot work on ranges.\n\nHence the \"Transform into a `formatexpr`\" part, I assumed it would be possible with some changes, and maybe a fun contribution\n\n\n> If you don't want to run this as an external tool, just define a user command that runs this on the current buffer and reloads.\n\nThat is possible yeah, but I don't think it defeats the point of this issue\n\n\n> queries should be provided to nvim-treesitter first, anyway, which already ships the formatter. \n\nI'm talking about query files in general, whether it be for personal use, plugin development or whatever.\nI believe a good and endorsed formatter would be nice to have by default for any query.\nPlus we already have indenting and linting; formatting seems like the final missing piece :)",
